originalText.text: I should check the review before doing my laundry here. The lady there was rude and not professional. This place is overcharged and they won’t allow you to use smaller washer and force you to use more expensive washer. You need to pay $6 to get a card. When I finish my laundry and she said she can’t return the money. She said you bought the card today and why you return the card today? That’s so so so rude!!! Your store closes at 8:30 pm and why you said you can’t return the charge for the card if I came at 7:50 pm? Will never come back again to wash my clothes here.

originalText.text: Overcharge!! We have trusted this place and always did laundry here, but they overcharged the wash&fold service. It marked $1.5 per pound and we had 13 pounds today. They charged us $24.5. After we found out and tried to let the lady fixed the price, the lady got angry and refused to do wash and fold for us. You can adjust the price if you wanna make more, but please don’t do it in this filthy way! We never checked the scale before and who knows how much we overpaid every time. They are not the only laundry here and what they did is a pure crime. If anyone do wash and fold, please check the scale and don’t waste your money.

originalText.text:
DO NOT!! I REPEAT
DO NOT COME TO THIS LAUNDROMAT!!!
LAUNDRY LADY HAS A VERY NASTY ATTITUDE!! I came in to wash 6 loads of laundry today to find out when my clothes where finished washing that there were only 4 working dryers!!! and all of the other dryers where out of service!! like literally 10 dryers out of service! I tell her I need 6 because I washed 6, she goes to tell me she is using two and I can only use one!!! Like how? My clothes where all wet and she goes to tell me what do I want her to do about it!! Honestly I’ve never felt so disrespected the fact that there was no consideration as to letting us costumers know that there are basically no dryers in service!! I had to literally take all my wet clothes to another laundromat and wash them again so I can use there dryers!! I was beyond livid. Spending $30 bucks to wash and being told to wait a hour for one dryer is beyond disrespectful they shouldn’t even be in service!!!!!! A simple note to customers about the dryers would of simply avoided this unfortunate situation IM NEVER GOING THERE AGAIN!!!
